# TheButler Project Structure

## Overview
TheButler is an Angular 20.1 application using modern standalone components and zoneless change detection.

## Project Architecture
- **Entry Point**: [main.ts](mdc:src/main.ts) bootstraps the application
- **App Component**: [app.ts](mdc:src/app/app.ts) is the root component
- **App Configuration**: [app.config.ts](mdc:src/app/app.config.ts) provides application-wide configuration
- **Routing**: [app.routes.ts](mdc:src/app/app.routes.ts) defines application routes
- **Global Styles**: [styles.scss](mdc:src/styles.scss) contains global styles
- **Angular Config**: [angular.json](mdc:angular.json) defines build and serve configurations

## Key Features
- **Zoneless Change Detection**: Uses `provideZonelessChangeDetection()` instead of Zone.js
- **Standalone Components**: No NgModules, all components are standalone
- **Signals**: Uses Angular signals for reactive state management
- **SCSS**: SCSS is the default styling approach

## Directory Structure
```
src/
  app/
    *.ts         - Component/service/directive TypeScript files
    *.html       - Component templates (separate template files)
    *.scss       - Component styles
    *.spec.ts    - Unit tests
  index.html     - HTML entry point
  main.ts        - Application bootstrap
  styles.scss    - Global styles
```

## Component Prefix
All component selectors should use the `app` prefix (e.g., `app-root`, `app-header`).
